  "system": {
    "short_name": "Recon",
    "short_description": "The Best Way In, Way Through, And Way Past",
    "description": "<p>Clearing the way isn't what you do. Why go through the trouble when there are ways unseen? A person just needs the right point of view to see them.</p>",
    "journal_description": "<p>I like hearing about the Doctors Beyond Stars and Cirque du Soldat from Dredge and Tower. I'm a little jealous too. I've finally gotten to see Journey City and the tower up close with the Cenotaph, but compared to the others I've barely seen anything. I wonder what it's like exploring all over, ignoring faction lines, bringing help and entertainment instead of guns and trouble. The thought that a town would be excited to see outsiders, that sticks with me. What if I had gotten to be a part of a squad like that? Bert's too loud and slow, but maybe I wouldn't even need an AWV with them.</p>",
    "experience_clues": "<p>- Execute a successful Reconnaissance, Espionage, Sabotage or Theft operation.<br>- Face off against challenges above your pay grade.<br>- Bolster your squad's reputation or develop a new one.<br>- Express the goals, inner conflict, or essential nature of the squad.</p>",
